          <change when="2014-10-30T05:47:45.501-04:00"
                 who="https://papyri.info/editor/users/simoeis">Vote - AcceptText - I would render this with reg tag minus the pointy brackets → &lt;:πρὸς σέ|reg|πρὸς έ:&gt; (one could of course represent the haplography also as &lt;:πρὸς σέ|reg|πρὸ σέ:&gt; or simply &lt;:πρὸς σέ|reg|προσε:&gt;). BL reading in ln 5 is fine. As for κατ᾽ ἐμὲ̣, it is difficult to verify this on the small photo in the ed.pr., but on the basis of the parallels cited, I am willing to accept it.</change>
